	<body>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 23" type="calendarDay" name="23" >
				<outline text="My reaction: in order for there to be &quot;unbiased&quot; journalists, there have to be &quot;biased&quot; ones, those who are cast out of the club of the distanced and the viewless. That's part of what you see going on here. Identity fortification at her expense. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/timmarchman/status/1418551573890932739&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 23 Jul 2021 18:48:19 GMT" tweetId="1418644160052187142" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1418644160052187142" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="The reason they do not explain the reason is that it would sound awkward and indefensible. Goes like this. &quot;We deal in perception. And the perception would be: this thing is one-sided.&quot; As Cillizza said: &quot;dooms even the possibility of the committee being perceived as bipartisan.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/newrepublic/status/1418609588664819713&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 23 Jul 2021 17:18:56 GMT" tweetId="1418621665316065282" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1418621665316065282" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 21" type="calendarDay" name="21" >
				<outline text="I like how @chrislhayes put it. Fox show hosts are not so much anti-vax as anti pro-vax. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mediaite.com/tv/chris-hayes-rips-cowardly-fox-news-hosts-for-vaccine-commentary-nihilistic-cynicism-and-preening-idiocy/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 18:29:48 GMT" tweetId="1417914723006308354" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417914723006308354" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="This is why I keep returning to critiques of the savvy style. It allows the writers of political news to bracket questions of truth and default to analysis of the game.
 
Thread. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/tzimmer_history/status/1417917352985907201&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 20:39:10 GMT" tweetId="1417947278829105164" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417947278829105164" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="There are some stories — and this is one — that reveal the political press, rather than the other way around. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/timodc/status/1417942412798746624&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 21:08:59 GMT" tweetId="1417954784510873607" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1417954784510873607" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 22" type="calendarDay" name="22" >
				<outline text="I always read job descriptions for the little hints they provide about a shifting industry, and the way the bosses are thinking about the workers— and the work. &lt;a href=&quot;https://nbcnewsdigitaljobs.com/work-here&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/tOgq63O6zW" type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 16:18:52 GMT" tweetId="1418244160138665984" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1418244160138665984" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Excellent questions, Greg. &quot;What would it take to make it credible to the GOP?&quot; and... &quot;Are these defensible demands?&quot; The banality of bipartisanship would be harder to sustain if the insider press had to begin that way. Read his thread. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ThePlumLineGS/status/1418226531042725888&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 16:34:11 GMT" tweetId="1418248016792887297" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1418248016792887297" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				<outline text="Politico's Playbook: Adding Jim Jordon to the investigation makes the results harder to dismiss for people who aren’t Team Blue. I see how this works for people who are reporters. For everyone else: how does successfully sown chaos become MORE convincing? &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.politico.com/newsletters/playbook/2021/07/22/return-of-the-masks-493689&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/wpoGi9G1P2" type="tweet" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 17:46:09 GMT" tweetId="1418266125641601027" urltweet="https://twitter.com/jayrosen_nyu/status/1418266125641601027" tweetUserName="jayrosen_nyu" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		</body>
	</opml>
